results.notes:
Over the past 10 years, I see this single fungi once or twice about every 3 years or so, at the base of a possibly (Grey Box).
The area is Eucalyptus rainforest, and the Tree is on the bank of a freshwater stream.
The fungi is always a very dark brown to black, and is attached to the tree at earth level. Pores are Maze-Like. The stipe when cut depicts a woody feature. I have had comments that this fungi when previously loaded was old, but this is definitely not the case. I frequent this spot once a week and always check the tree and its surrounding base area.
I believe from the images and the texture that the fungi is a polypore. At the time of collection, the fungi cap was between hard & soft, (not like a standard polypore texture or Bracket fungi). I am really interested to progress past Polypore sensu lato if possible. I have not been able to find an image that matches this fungi.
